  "texts": [
    "This information can be coded jointly or separately, using either lossless or lossy computer techniques [211].Challenges encountered in the compression task include computational costs, support for incrementally acquired data, local decompression, geometry resolution, and managing the points' number.",
    "The geometry of objects is sometimes based on sparse signals, resulting in information distributed across an irregular sparse domain with irregular neighborhoods.",
    "As a result, compression may lead to feature loss, making object identification difficult.",
    "For this reason, DL methods based on coarse-to-fine geometry are employed to tackle these problems.",
    "Besides, DL methods are further differentiated according to the encoding domain and prior information."
  ],
